  "datePublished": "2026-03-08",
  "description": "llama.cpp is an open-source C/C++ implementation of large language model inference, originally built for Meta\u0026rsquo;s Llama models but now supporting most open-weight model architectures. It is the inference engine underneath Ollama.\nllama.cpp was created to run LLMs on consumer hardware — particularly CPUs — without requiring Python, CUDA, or other heavy dependencies. It reads models in GGUF format and supports quantization from 2-bit to 8-bit, making it possible to run 7B-parameter models on machines with 8 GB of RAM.\n",
